      "title": "Diamond Number Pyramid Pattern",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": false,
      "shortest": false,
      "solution": "import java.util.*;\n\nclass Solution {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);\n        int n = sc.nextInt();\n       \n        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n            String str = \"\";\n            str += (\" \".repeat(n - i - 1));\n            for (int j = 0; j < 2 * i + 1; j++) {\n                int val = (j > i) ? (3 * i + 1 - j) : (i + 1 + j);\n                str += val;\n            }\n            System.out.println(str);\n        }\n\n        for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {\n            String str = \"\";\n\n            str += (\" \".repeat(n - i - 1));\n            for (int j = 0; j < 2 * i + 1; j++) {\n                int val = (j > i) ? (3 * i + 1 - j) : (i + 1 + j);\n                str += val;\n            }\n            System.out.println(str);\n        }\n    }\n}",
      "statement": "Given an integer n, print a symmetric diamond-shaped number pattern.\n\nThe pattern starts from 1 at the top.\nEach row expands outward with increasing numbers and then mirrors back.\nThe middle row contains the largest sequence.\nThe pattern is vertically symmetric.",
